        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "I just noticed a strange Zend_Date::isDate behavior that didn't occur before.\nHave a look at the following code:\n\n{code}\nif (Zend_Date::isDate('2007-11-14 21:06:36 GMT')) {\n    echo 'true';\n} else {\n    echo 'false';\n}\n{code}\n\nIt prints false.\nWhat makes everything strange, is that the following piece of code works well.\n\n{code}\n$x = new Zend_Date('2007-11-14 21:06:36 GMT');\necho $x; \/\/ Nov 14, 2007 9:06:36 PM\n{code}\n\nAs I told before, this is a new issue.\nThe last time I tested Zend_Date \/trunk (02\/Jan\/08) it worked without any problem."
        },
